21) We Can get the Emails which are NOT Following the below mentioned Rules

SELECT * FROM users WHERE email NOT REGEXP '^[a-z0-9._]+@[a-z0-9_]+\.[a-z] {2, }$’;




Output - 

+----+----------------------------------+
| id | email                            |
+----+----------------------------------+
|  4 | invalid-email@example            |
|  9 | invalid-email@.com               |
| 13 | invalid-email@example..com       |
| 15 | valid.email+alias@example.org    |
| 20 | invalid-email@example@domain.com |
+----+----------------------------------+










22) A) If we Want an Email where there is Exactly 20 Characters Then We can use below Command

SELECT * FROM users WHERE email REGEXP ‘^………………..$’;



Output - 

+----+----------------------+
| id | email                |
+----+----------------------+
|  1 | john.doe@example.com |
+----+----------------------+







22) B) If we Want an Email where there is Exactly 20 Characters Using LIKE Operator then we can use below Command

SELECT * FROM users WHERE email LIKE '____________________';



Output - 

+----+----------------------+
| id | email                |
+----+----------------------+
|  1 | john.doe@example.com |
+----+----------------------+









