24) We want Name which Should Not Contain "_", "-"

SELECT * FROM users WHERE email REGEXP '^[^_-]+@[a-z0-9_]+\.[a-z]{5}$’;




Output - 

+----+-------------------------------+
| id | email                         |
+----+-------------------------------+
| 18 | arthur.curry@atlantis.ocean   |
| 22 | hal.jordan@greenlantern.space |
+----+-------------------------------+






Note -

If we Give This "^" Symbol Inside a Square Bracket [] that means the Email will Not Contain "_" & "-" As Shown Above



. Matches Any Single Character

^ Matches the Start of the String

$ Matches the End of the String

[] - defines a character class to match any single character within the brackets

* + ? - Quantifiers to Specify Number of Occurrences

? Means Zero Or One Time
* Means Zero Or Any Number of Times
+ Means One Or More Time










